# Output Structure

Each contrast produces:
- means → estimated marginal means
- contrasts → statistical comparisons
- weights → (for overall model only)

```text
amyloid_effect_contrasts.csv
disease_effect_contrasts.csv
overall_effect_contrasts.csv
max_pathology_effect_contrasts.csv
overall_effect_region_weights.csv
```

The region heterogeneity test produces:
```text
region_heterogeneity_interaction_tests.csv
region_heterogeneity_posthoc.csv
```

The co-occurrence analysis produces:
```text
celltype_cooccurrence_by_region.csv
```

A unified summary table is generated:

```text
combined_spatial_contrast_summary.csv
```
Containing:
- celltype
- region
- contrast
- contrast_type
- log2_OR
- p-value
- adjusted p-value

